comment._content: C. Sugden, Tobacconist and Hairdresser. (See signage on wall of building). [http://www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw/9388956366/] Location is Parramatta Rd, Five Dock (between Ashfield and Drummoyne), near Croydon Rd. - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/16324247 [see "Businesses for sale", 1st column]. Sugden was still there in May 1932 - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/46653218

comment._content: Something to do with resumptions for street widening of Parramatta Road?

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: 3 January 1930 was a Friday.  It is amazing that such a hideous streetscape is full of interesting things.  Those poles look very tall to me.  Maybe because there are no trees to soften the lines.

comment._content: I have checked the 1943 aerial shots on maps.six.nsw.gov.au/ and it seems by '43 Parramatta Road has been widened. This is suggested as the current 2013 alignment in this area is consistent with the 1943 imagery/alignment.
